info.title: CISCO-OSPF-MIB MIB API
info.description:
An extension to the MIB module defined in
    RFC 1850 for managing OSPF implimentation. 
    Most of the MIB definitions are based on
    the IETF draft 
    < draft-ietf-ospf-mib-update-05.txt > . 
    Support for OSPF Sham link is also added

⚠️ **IMPORTANT - MIB DATA ACCESS**:
This YANG model exists for SMIv2-to-YANG translation purposes, but MIB data on IOS-XE devices is primarily accessed via **SNMP protocol**, not RESTCONF.

**RESTCONF Limitation**: Many MIB paths may return 404 errors via RESTCONF `/data` endpoints because the device exposes MIB data through SNMP, not the YANG datastore.

**Recommended Access Methods**:
- Use SNMP (v2c/v3) to query MIB data directly
- Use NETCONF `<get>` operations for devices supporting YANG-modeled MIB access
- Check device capabilities: some newer IOS-XE versions may support limited RESTCONF access to specific MIBs

**YANG Model Purpose**: These YANG models define the structure of SNMP MIBs in YANG format for tooling compatibility, but do not guarantee RESTCONF data availability.

get.description: Retrieve cospfGeneralGroup operational data from MIB

cospfRFC1583Compatibility.description:
Indicates metrics used to choose among multiple AS-
          external-LSAs. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to
          enabled, only cost will be used when choosing among
          multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same
          destination. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to
          disabled, preference will be driven first by type of
          path using cost only to break ties.

cospfOpaqueLsaSupport.description: The router's support for Opaque LSA types.

cospfTrafficEngineeringSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF traffic engineering.

cospfOpaqueASLsaCount.description:
The total number of Opaque AS link-state
          advertisements in the link state database.

cospfOpaqueASLsaCksumSum.description:
The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Opaque AS 
          link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained
          link state database.

get.description: Retrieve cospfLsdbTable operational data from MIB

schema.description:
The OSPF Process's Link State Database. This 
        table is meant for Opaque LSA's

cospfLsdbType.description:
The type of the link state advertisement.
            Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

cospfLsdbSequence.description:
The sequence number field is a  signed  32-bit
            integer.   It  is used to detect old and duplicate
            link state advertisements.  The  space  of
            sequence  numbers  is  linearly  ordered.   The
            larger the sequence number the more recent  the
            advertisement.

cospfLsdbAge.description:
This field is the age of the link state advertisement in
            seconds.

cospfLsdbChecksum.description:
This field is the  checksum  of  the  complete
            contents  of  the  advertisement, excepting the
            age field.  The age field is excepted  so  that
            an   advertisement's  age  can  be  incremented
            without updating the  checksum.   The  checksum
            used  is  the same that is used for ISO connectionless
            datagrams; it is commonly referred  to
            as the Fletcher checksum.

cospfLsdbAdvertisement.description:
The entire Link State Advertisement, including
            its header.

get.description: Retrieve cospfShamLinkTable operational data from MIB

schema.description: Information about this router's sham links

cospfShamLinkEntry.description: Information about a single sham link

cospfShamLinkAreaId.description:
The  Transit  Area  that  the   Virtual   Link
            traverses.  By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

cospfShamLinkLocalIpAddress.description: The Local IP address of the sham link.

cospfShamLinkNeighborId.description:
The Router ID of the other end router of the sham
            link.

cospfShamLinkRetransInterval.description:
The number of seconds between  link-state  advertisement
            retransmissions,  for  adjacencies
            belonging to this  link.   This  value  is also
            used when retransmitting database description  
            and  link-state  request  packets. This value  
            should  be well over the expected round trip
            time.

cospfShamLinkHelloInterval.description:
The length of time, in  seconds,  between  the
            Hello  packets that the router sends on the sham
            link.

cospfShamLinkRtrDeadInterval.description:
The number of seconds that  a  router's  Hello
            packets  have  not been seen before it's neighbors
            declare the router down.  This  should  be
            some  multiple  of  the  Hello  interval.

cospfShamLinkEvents.description:
The number of state changes or error events on
            this sham link

get.description: Retrieve cospfLocalLsdbTable operational data from MIB

schema.description:
The OSPF Process's Link-Local Link State Database
        for non-virtual links.

cospfLocalLsdbIpAddress.description:
The IP Address of the interface from
            which the LSA was received if the interface is
            numbered.

cospfLocalLsdbAddressLessIf.description:
The Interface Index of the interface from
            which the LSA was received if the interface is
            unnumbered.

cospfLocalLsdbType.description:
The type of the link state advertisement.
            Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

cospfLocalLsdbLsid.description:
The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field
            containing a 32 bit identifier in IP address format;
            it identifies the piece of the routing domain
            that is being described by the advertisement.

cospfLocalLsdbRouterId.description:
The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the
            originating router in the Autonomous System.

cospfLocalLsdbSequence.description:
The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit
            integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link
            state advertisements. The space of
            sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The
            larger the sequence number the more recent the
            advertisement.

cospfLocalLsdbAge.description:
This field is the age of the link state advertisement 
            in seconds.

cospfLocalLsdbChecksum.description:
This field is the checksum of the complete
            contents of the advertisement, excepting the
            age field. The age field is excepted so that
            an advertisement's age can be incremented
            without updating the checksum. The checksum
            used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless
            datagrams; it is commonly referred  to
            as the Fletcher checksum.

cospfLocalLsdbAdvertisement.description:
The entire Link State Advertisement, including
            its header.

get.description: Retrieve cospfShamLinkNbrTable operational data from MIB

schema.description: A table of sham link neighbor information.

cospfShamLinkNbrArea.description: The area to which the sham link is part of.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddrType.description:
The type of internet address of this sham link neighbor's
            IP address.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this sham link neighbor is using.

cospfShamLinkNbrRtrId.description:
A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring
            router.

cospfShamLinkNbrOptions.description:
A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options
            field.
            
            Bit 1, if set, indicates that the  system  will
            operate  on  Type of Service metrics other than
            TOS 0.  If zero, the neighbor will  ignore  all
            metrics except the TOS 0 metric.
            
            Bit 2, if set, indicates  that  the  system  is
            Network  Multicast  capable; ie, that it implements 
            OSPF Multicast Routing.

cospfShamLinkNbrState.description:
The state of this sham link neighbor relation-
            ship.

cospfShamLinkNbrEvents.description:
The number of  times  this sham link has changed
            state or an error has occurred.

cospfShamLinkNbrLsRetransQLen.description:
The  current  length  of  the   retransmission
            queue. The retransmission queue is maintained for
            LSAs that have been flooded but not acknowledged
            on this adjacency.

cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed.description:
Indicates whether Hellos are being  suppressed
            to the neighbor.

get.description: Retrieve cospfShamLinksTable operational data from MIB

schema.description: Information about this router's sham links.

cospfShamLinksEntry.description: Information about a single sham link.

cospfShamLinksAreaId.description: The area that this sham link is part of.

cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddrType.description:
The type of internet address of this sham link's local IP
            address.

cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddr.description: The Local IP address of the sham link.

cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddrType.description:
The type of internet address of this sham link's remote IP
            address.

cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddr.description: The IP address of the other end router of the sham link.

cospfShamLinksRetransInterval.description:
The number of seconds between  link-state  advertisement
            retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this link.
            This value is also used when retransmitting database 
            description and link-state request packets. This value
            should be well over the expected round trip time.

cospfShamLinksHelloInterval.description:
The length of time, in  seconds,  between  the
            Hello  packets that the router sends on the sham
            link.

cospfShamLinksRtrDeadInterval.description:
The number of seconds that  a  router's  Hello
            packets  have  not been seen before it's neighbors
            declare the router down.  This  should  be
            some  multiple  of  the  Hello  interval.

cospfShamLinksEvents.description:
The number of state changes or error events on
            this sham link

            retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this link.
            This value is also used when retransmitting database 
            description and link-state request packets. This value
            should be well over the expected round trip time.

cospfShamLinksHelloInterval.description:
The length of time, in  seconds,  between  the
            Hello  packets that the router sends on the sham
            link.

cospfShamLinksRtrDeadInterval.description:
The number of seconds that  a  router's  Hello
            packets  have  not been seen before it's neighbors
            declare the router down.  This  should  be
            some  multiple  of  the  Hello  interval.

cospfShamLinksEvents.description:
The number of state changes or error events on
            this sham link

get.description: Retrieve list of cospfLsdbEntry entries from MIB

cospfLsdbType.description:
The type of the link state advertisement.
            Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

cospfLsdbSequence.description:
The sequence number field is a  signed  32-bit
            integer.   It  is used to detect old and duplicate
            link state advertisements.  The  space  of
            sequence  numbers  is  linearly  ordered.   The
            larger the sequence number the more recent  the
            advertisement.

cospfLsdbAge.description:
This field is the age of the link state advertisement in
            seconds.

cospfLsdbChecksum.description:
This field is the  checksum  of  the  complete
            contents  of  the  advertisement, excepting the
            age field.  The age field is excepted  so  that
            an   advertisement's  age  can  be  incremented
            without updating the  checksum.   The  checksum
            used  is  the same that is used for ISO connectionless
            datagrams; it is commonly referred  to
            as the Fletcher checksum.

cospfLsdbAdvertisement.description:
The entire Link State Advertisement, including
            its header.

cospfShamLinkNbrArea.description: The area to which the sham link is part of.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddrType.description:
The type of internet address of this sham link neighbor's
            IP address.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this sham link neighbor is using.

cospfShamLinkNbrRtrId.description:
A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring
            router.

cospfShamLinkNbrOptions.description:
A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options
            field.
            
            Bit 1, if set, indicates that the  system  will
            operate  on  Type of Service metrics other than
            TOS 0.  If zero, the neighbor will  ignore  all
            metrics except the TOS 0 metric.
            
            Bit 2, if set, indicates  that  the  system  is
            Network  Multicast  capable; ie, that it implements 
            OSPF Multicast Routing.

cospfShamLinkNbrState.description:
The state of this sham link neighbor relation-
            ship.

cospfShamLinkNbrEvents.description:
The number of  times  this sham link has changed
            state or an error has occurred.

cospfShamLinkNbrLsRetransQLen.description:
The  current  length  of  the   retransmission
            queue. The retransmission queue is maintained for
            LSAs that have been flooded but not acknowledged
            on this adjacency.

cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed.description:
Indicates whether Hellos are being  suppressed
            to the neighbor.

cospfRFC1583Compatibility.description:
Indicates metrics used to choose among multiple AS-
          external-LSAs. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to
          enabled, only cost will be used when choosing among
          multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same
          destination. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to
          disabled, preference will be driven first by type of
          path using cost only to break ties.

A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options
            field.
            
            Bit 1, if set, indicates that the  system  will
            operate  on  Type of Service metrics other than
            TOS 0.  If zero, the neighbor will  ignore  all
            metrics except the TOS 0 metric.
            
            Bit 2, if set, indicates  that  the  system  is
            Network  Multicast  capable; ie, that it implements 
            OSPF Multicast Routing.

            queue. The retransmission queue is maintained for
            LSAs that have been flooded but not acknowledged
            on this adjacency.

cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed.description:
Indicates whether Hellos are being  suppressed
            to the neighbor.
